@ultrabug using a custom hash function. `hash_fn` doesn't seem to be used despite being documented in the readme. Here are all references to `hash_fn`:
https://github.com/ultrabug/uhashring/blob/a1e10ba7a451d3763a4f8f5fc28e853a2e41cba8/uhashring/ring_meta.py#L22
https://github.com/ultrabug/uhashring/blob/a1e10ba7a451d3763a4f8f5fc28e853a2e41cba8/uhashring/ring.py#L32

The value that is being returned is the amount of time that the stack expects to be able to wait until it should break out of the `select()` call inside the `run()` function and do something else that is scheduled as a "task".  The actual delay passed to `select()` is the `delta`.  There is a variable called `sleeptime` which is passed to the `time.sleep()` function, the side effect is releasing the interpreter to give time to other threads.  If you call `enable_sleeping()` before calling `run()` then every time through the run loop other threads can get time.

So try a couple things; first, try calling `enable_sleeping()` before `run()` and see if the run function is starving another thread, but it also seems likely that the flip side is happening, i.e., the other thread is starving `run()`.  You can also try passing a very small value to the `spin` parameter of run which will shrink the amount of time the thread stays inside the `select()` call.

