Ok, so what I was trying to say is that in the following check
```
     if (PyObject_HasAttr((PyObject *)Py_TYPE(self), name))
         return PyObject_GenericSetAttr((PyObject *)self, name, value);
```
in that check `PyObject_HasAttr((PyObject *)Py_TYPE(self), name)` will be true. Therefore the `PyObject_RichCompareBool(name, wrapped_str, Py_EQ) == 1` check is unnecessary.

