Anyways, to your issue. This is a result of our poor support (at the moment) for intrinsic functions. Currently, we are validating that the ReadCapacityUnits and WriteCapacityUnits' values are int. In your case, they are strings. We should totally be supporting intrinsics in this case. We started realizing this some time ago and have tried to make additions to the template compatible with intrinsics to start but we haven't yet gone back to all the existing ones (one of them being SimpleTable). Glancing at the code, this doesn't seem like a huge change at all. I can't promise I will get to it right away (juggling a couple different things at the moment) but will see how I can get this prioritized in the near future. I will comment back when I start to work on this.

As far as a workaround: Sadly, hardcoding the capacity as a number in the resource is the best I have to offer.

