@petevg I'm not a big fan of having the implementation be dynamically loaded at run-time.  It makes it hard to know what params to pass to the facades, whether by introspection, reading the source, or reading generated docs.  Also, if / when https://bugs.launchpad.net/juju/+bug/1679438 happens, we should be using that schema definition directly and shouldn't even need schemagen or schema JSON files in the libjuju repo anymore.

Instead, I'd prefer to split `_client.py` into separate packages for each facade with a file for each version of the facade but still have them pre-generated.  We could even have an optimization that only looks for new versions of facades that don't have implementations and don't bother regenerating existing versions.  I think this gives us a natural place to put generated docstrings, makes the params very explicit, and should give us nice commits that make it very clear what's new.  It would also make it easy to diff two versions of a facade to see what changed.  I think the import logic would work pretty much how you described for loading the versioned schema in the pastebin.

Does that seem like a reasonable counter-proposal?

