The feature is not hard but turn the way the code works around, so it will not be a small patch. Furthermore after thought, I believe the send/receive options should be set per process for finer grained control. So it may end up being.
```
process announce-routes {
   run /run.me;
   encoder json;
}

neighbor ip {
   process announce-routes {
      send {
          open;
      }
      receive {
         packets;
         consolidate;
         open;
         update;
      }
   }
}
```


```
process announce-routes {
   run /run.me;
   encoder json;
}

group notified {
   process announce-routes {
      send {
          open;
      }
      receive {
         packets;
         consolidate;
         open;
         update;
      }
      neighbor ip {
      }
      neighbor ip {
      }
   }
}
```

Due to the current parser however, it is likely that the process group will need to be created before the neighbor and that having group { neighbor, process, neighbor } will only add the process communication to the second neighbor only.

